{"session_id": 56, "bill_id": 18987, "bill_type": "Senate Bill", "bill_number": 82, "bill_title": "require prior notice of automatic renewal dates in certain telecommunications contracts.", "sponsors": [{"legislator_profile_id": 3057, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3093, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3044, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3059, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3070, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3099, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3113, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3149, "is_prime": false}], "keywords": ["Contracts", "Public Utilities and Carriers"], "audio": [{"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-26T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sju09sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-26T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sju09sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-26T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sju09sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sju11sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sju11sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sju11sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sju11sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sju11sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-30T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sen13.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-12T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/hco23sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-12T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/hco23sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-12T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/hco23sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-12T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/hco23sb0082a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 18987, "bill_version_id": 99396, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2004-01-21T09:01:47-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require prior notice of automatic renewal dates in certain telecommunications contracts. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 49-31 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any telecommunications company having a contract with a subscriber for any retail telecommunications service that has a term of one year or more and that contains a provision requiring the subscriber to take any action to avoid automatic renewal of the contract, shall give prior written notice to the subscriber of the action that the subscriber must take to avoid automatic renewal. The telecommunications company shall give notice to the subscriber not less than thirty and not more than sixty days before the date of the required action. The notice shall inform the subscriber in clear, plain language what action the subscriber must take to avoid renewal and the date by which the subscriber must take such action. If the company fails to give the notice required by this section, the automatic renewal provision may not be enforced against the subscriber, and the subscriber may terminate the contract at will following expiration of the original term without incurring any liability or penalty for early termination."}, {"bill_id": 18987, "bill_version_id": 100188, "bill_version": "Senate Judiciary Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2004-01-28T16:06:34-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require prior notice of automatic renewal dates in certain telecommunications contracts. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 49-31 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any telecommunications company having a contract with a subscriber for any retail telecommunications service that has a term of one year or more and that contains a provision requiring the subscriber to take any action to avoid automatic renewal of the contract for a renewal term greater than sixty days, shall give prior written notice to the subscriber of the action that the subscriber must take to avoid automatic renewal. The telecommunications company shall give notice to the subscriber not less than thirty and not more than sixty days before the date of the required action. The notice shall inform the subscriber in clear, plain and conspicuous language what action the subscriber must take to avoid renewal and the date by which the subscriber must take such action. If the company fails to give the notice required by this section, the automatic renewal provision may not be enforced against the subscriber, and the subscriber may terminate the contract at will following expiration of the original term without incurring any liability or penalty for early termination. The commission may promulgate rules pursuant to chapter 1-26 concerning the form, content, and means of delivery of the notice required by this section."}, {"bill_id": 18987, "bill_version_id": 101378, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2004-02-17T08:58:41-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amen